independent_work.et:
Students will be evaluated on the basis of (1) seven quizzes; (2) groupwork assignments for seminars, (3) fieldwork assignments, and (4) the qualitative/interpretive research design. The distribution of the final course grade is as follows:

- 7x2 points for quizzes (14% of the total grade);
- 21 points for a group work assignment (21% of the total grade);
- 25 points for the fieldwork assignment (25% of the total grade);
- 40 points for the qualitative/Interpretive Research Design (40% of the total grade);
- Participation in online discussion forums (minimum in 5 of 7 of them in order to be eligible for a final grade).
- Class attendance (minimum in 80% of lectures and seminars combined in order to be eligible for a final grade).

Detailed information on each of the assignments is provided on the course's Moodle page.

debt_elimination.et:
No extensions are allowed for the quizzes;
No extensions are allowed for group work assignments;
Late submissions for the fieldwork assignment are allowed with some penalty. Extensions without penalty are possible under stipulated conditions on Moodle;
Late submissions for the qualitative/interpretive research design are allowed with some penalty. Extensions without penalty are possible under stipulated conditions on Moodle.
